laboratory_examinations.findings: Initially 7.0 to 8.3 µg/ml, elevated to 10.8 µg/ml after introducing nefazodone, later reduced to 7.4 µg/ml after dosage adjustment.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Carbamazepine levels increased after the introduction of nefazodone from 7.0-8.3 µg/ml to 10.8 µg/ml, then decreased to 7.4 µg/ml after reducing the dose.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Initially ranged between 5.2 and 6.2 µg/ml; elevated to 15.1 µg/ml after nefazodone treatment.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Carbamazepine levels increased to 15.1 µg/ml 14 days after starting nefazodone; subsequently decreased to 5.8 µg/ml after dose reduction.
